Career Development

Our Values











WHY USG
USG has been named...
Top Workplace by the Detroit Free Press (three years in a row) 
2016 Illinois Workplace Achiever by the Chicago Tribune
Alfred P. Sloan award for excellence in workplace effectiveness and flexibility
100 Best Managed Companies, IndustryWeek
Top 25 Places to Work (recognized twice), Chicago Magazine
America’s Most Admired Companies by Fortune magazine
Three time winner of the Chicago Innovation Awards
For over one hundred and ten years, USG has meant building —
  providing products that help build shelter for the world, building a
  leadership position in our industry, building strong relationships
  with our stakeholders and building rewarding careers for employees.
We Build Shelter
Our products provide high quality, low cost building solutions, and
  protection from fire, noise, and the elements. Our manufacturing
  processes are environmentally friendly using 100% recycled paper and
  synthetic gypsum, a by-product of the process used for reducing power
  plant emissions. USG, through its subsidiaries and the USG Foundation
  contribute to many charitable causes, particularly those involved in
  homelessness, housing, and disaster relief.
We Build Careers
We hire people for careers, not jobs. We invest in employees through
  classroom and on-the-job training. We promote from within wherever
  possible and we are not afraid to give employees significant
  responsibility early in their careers. We move people across
  businesses, functions, and across the country to make the best use of
  their talents. We have an on-line job posting program to let employees
  know what opportunities are available in the Company and to match the
  right person with the right position. USG is a Company in which
  everyone can reach their full potential, which is why most of our
  leadership came up through the ranks. Our employees are the best in
  the industry, which is why USG Corporation is the industry leader year
  after year!
Be part of the Team - Build your future at USG.


Click here for jobs in the United States


Click 
here for jobs in Canada
Job Scam Using USG’s Name
USG Corporation has been informed of fraudulent emails referencing
  part-time work-from-home jobs at USG. These emails are part of a scam
  and do not come from USG or our affiliates. View
    an example fraudulent email. You can learn more by viewing
    this article.
If you receive a similar email, do not respond to it. Instead,
  forward it to spam@uce.gov. If you
  have already received a check in the mail, do not cash it. Notify
    the U.S. Postal
    Inspection Service. If you have lost money to fraud, contact
  your local authorities and report it to the Internet Crime Complaint Center.












